body:
Given

```rust
fn foo(_: &dyn std::error::Error) {}

enum E {
    A(Box<dyn std::error::Error>),
}
fn bar(e: &E) {
    match e {
        E::A(err) => {
            foo(err);
        }
    }
}
```

[`rustc` currently emits](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=a67a4175d237081471dc60cbd5aea953)

```
error[E0277]: the size for values of type `(dyn std::error::Error + 'static)` cannot be known at compilation time
 --> src/main.rs:9:17
  |
9 |             foo(err);
  |                 ^^^ doesn't have a size known at compile-time
  |
  = help: the trait `Sized` is not implemented for `(dyn std::error::Error + 'static)`
  = note: required because of the requirements on the impl of `std::error::Error` for `Box<(dyn std::error::Error + 'static)>`
  = note: required for the cast to the object type `dyn std::error::Error`
```

Trying the usual go-to fixes ([`foo(&err)`](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=aa7e29118a0b702909015b1409ced9d8), [`foo(&*err)`](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=89e9d9e8f1b5d3049b24de9e388d891c)) produce further errors that aren't helpful either.

The solution to the code is to write [`foo(&**err)`](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=48e1e65c049117d9069c77d3a0356c9f) or [`foo(err.as_ref())`](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=ca4baa1bce9772ebb510a8d8a8e7864d). We already provide some suggestions for `foo(&err)`, `foo(*err)` and `foo(&*err)` when appropriate and this causes [general confusion to enough people](https://twitter.com/ekuber/status/1313177770659201024) that it would be good to extend that machinery to also handle this case, as well as improving the [`foo(&err)`](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=aa7e29118a0b702909015b1409ced9d8) and [`foo(&*err)`](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=89e9d9e8f1b5d3049b24de9e388d891c) cases.
